  "en_notes_yusuf": [
    {
      "note_no": "1607",
      "note": "The first word, Zafir, translated \"sighs\", is applied to one part in the process of the braying of an ass, when he emits a deep breath (Cf. 25:12). The second, Shahiq, translated \"sobs\", is the other process in the braying of an ass, when he draws in a long breath. This suggestion of an animal proverbial for his folly implies that the wicked, in spite of their arrogance and insolence in this world below, will at last realise that they have been fools after all, throwing away their own chances whenever they got diem. In 67:7 the word Shahiq is applied to the tremendous roaring intake or devouring of Hell-fire."
